<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="118" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="118">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="118">
The holotype of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Aelurillus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aelurillus steliosi" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="steliosi">Aelurillus steliosi</taxonomicName>
is conspecific with that of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Aelurillus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aelurillus leipoldae" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leipoldae">Aelurillus leipoldae</taxonomicName>
. Both specimens examined (the male holotypes of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Aelurillus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aelurillus leipoldae" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leipoldae">Aelurillus leipoldae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Aelurillus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aelurillus steliosi" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="steliosi">Aelurillus steliosi</taxonomicName>
) have the same body coloration and structure of the palpus and the embolic division (Figs 29-31 and see 
<bibRefCitation author="Azarkina, GN" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the British Arachnological Society" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" pagination="249 - 263" title="New and poorly known species of the genus Aelurillus Simon, 1884 from central Asia, Asia Minor and the eastern Mediterranean (Araneae: Salticidae)." volume="12" year="2002">Azarkina 2002</bibRefCitation>
: figs 31-38, 41; 
<bibRefCitation author="Dobroruka, LJ" journalOrPublisher="Biologia Gallo-hellenica" pageId="10" pageNumber="119" pagination="5 - 26" title="Notes on a collection of jumping spiders from Greece, mainly from Crete (Araneae: Salticidae)." volume="28" year="2002">Dobroruka 2002</bibRefCitation>
: figs 6-10). Therefore, it is safe to conclude that the name 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Aelurillus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aelurillus steliosi" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="steliosi">Aelurillus steliosi</taxonomicName>
Dobroruka, 2002 is a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Aelurillus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aelurillus leipoldae" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leipoldae">Aelurillus leipoldae</taxonomicName>
(Metzner, 1999), contrary to 
<bibRefCitation author="Bosmans, R" journalOrPublisher="Nieuwsbrief van de Belgische Arachnologische Vereniging" pageId="10" pageNumber="119" pagination="1 - 147" title="Spiders of Crete (araneae). A catalogue of all currently known species from the Greek island of Crete." volume="28" year="2013">Bosmans et al. (2013)</bibRefCitation>
(see also comment under 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Aelurillus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aelurillus cretensis" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cretensis">Aelurillus cretensis</taxonomicName>
) who synonymized 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Aelurillus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aelurillus steliosi" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="steliosi">Aelurillus steliosi</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Aelurillus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aelurillus cretensis" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cretensis">Aelurillus cretensis</taxonomicName>
Azarkina, 2002.
</paragraph>
